properties.Title: Update To Civil Emergency Alert Issued By Government Of Saskatchewan
properties.Summary:
Description: Update for the Civil Emergency Alert issued by the Government of Saskatchewan. The state of emergency in Saskatchewan remains in effect. UPDATE: Phase 2 of Re-Open Saskatchewan is effective May 19, 2020. All Public Health Orders continue to apply during the implementation of Phase 2 Re-Open Saskatchewan. People are being reminded to avoid unnecessary travel and stay home if you are sick or symptomatic. Public and private gatherings, inside and outside, are limited to more no more than 10 people and physical distancing by at least two metres from others is to be applied. Monitor and follow all public health orders on the Saskatchewan.ca COVID 19 website. Wash your hands often. Together, we are reducing the risk. We can pull together by staying apart.
Expires: 2020-05-25T17:00:00-06:00

properties.Title: Severe Thunderstorm Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: At 12:56 p.m. CST, Environment Canada meteorologists are tracking a severe thunderstorm capable of producing very strong wind gusts, up to nickel size hail and heavy rain. This severe thunderstorm is currently located west of Cantuar and is tracking to the north at 30 km/h. Nickel size hail was reported near Webb. ### Heavy downpours can cause flash floods and water pooling on roads. Large hail can damage property and cause injury. Strong wind gusts can toss loose objects, damage weak buildings, break branches off trees and overturn large vehicles. Remember, severe thunderstorms can produce tornadoes. Severe thunderstorm warnings are issued when imminent or occurring thunderstorms are likely to produce or are producing one or more of the following: large hail, damaging winds, torrential rainfall.

properties.Title: Blizzard Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Blizzard conditions with poor visibility in snow and blowing snow are expected or occurring. STrong northwesterly winds combined with falling snow will bring blizzard conditions to the Naujaat region tonight and Thursday. A disturbance tracking across the Foxe Basin is currently bringing moderate northwesterly winds to the Naujaat region with occasional poor visibilities in blowing snow. Winds are expected to intensify tonight and this along with falling snow will create blizzard conditions which will persist into Thursday. Conditions are expected to improve Thursday night as winds diminish. ### Travel is expected to be hazardous due to reduced visibility. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Title: Special Air Quality Statement In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Elevated pollution levels are expected or occurring. A wildfire located east of Prince Albert and north of Melfort is spreading smoke over north central portions of the grainbelt. Air quality in locations down wind of the fire will at times be poor. Northeasterly winds today will gradually shift to the south on Thursday moving the smoke out of the area and possibly into north central Saskatchewan. ### Individuals may experience symptoms such as increased coughing, throat irritation, headaches or shortness of breath. Children, seniors, and those with cardiovascular or lung disease, such as asthma, are especially at risk. People with lung diseases, such as asthma and COPD, can be particularly sensitive to air pollution. They will generally experience more serious health effects at lower levels. Pollution can aggravate their diseases, leading to increased medication use, doctor and emergency room visits, and hospital visits. Please call HealthLine 811 for advice on health risks, symptoms and precautions associated with air quality. Visit www.airhealth.ca for information on how to reduce your health risk and your personal contribution to pollution levels, as well as for current and forecast AQHI values. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada.
Expires: 2020-05-21T07:29:26-00:00

properties.Title: Freezing Rain Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Freezing rain is expected or occurring. A low pressure system tracking through Hudson Bay will bring a wintery mix of weather to communities in southern Baffin Island today. Freezing rain moved into Iqaluit early this morning and persist for a few hours before temperatures climb above freezing. The precipitation may be mixed with snow at times. Please refer to the public forecast for additional details. ### Freezing rain warnings are issued when rain falling in sub-zero temperatures creates ice build-up and icy surfaces. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Title: Snowfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Snowfall with total amounts of 15 to 25 cm is expected. Heavy snow expected in Pangnirtung Wednesday into Wednesday night. Heavy snow will move into the Pangnirtung region Wednesday morning and continue into Wednesday night. Total snowfall accumulations of 15 to 25 cm are possible by Thursday morning. Periods of light snow may persist in the region on Thursday however no further significant accumulation are expected. ### Rapidly accumulating snow could make travel difficult over some locations. Visibility may be suddenly reduced at times in heavy snow. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada.
